class MyOwnDataset(InMemoryDataset):
    def __init__(self, root,datalist ,num_train_per_class=140, num_val=500, num_test=1000, transform=None, pre_transform=None):
        self.num_train_per_class = num_train_per_class
        self.num_val = num_val
        self.num_test = num_test
        self.data_list = datalist
        super(MyOwnDataset, self).__init__(root, transform, pre_transform)
        self.data, self.slices = torch.load(self.processed_paths[0])

    @property
    def raw_file_names(self):
        return []

    @property
    def processed_file_names(self):
        return [r'.\muowndata.dataset']

    def download(self):
        # Download to `self.raw_dir`.
        # 我不需要下载，因此直接pass
        pass

    def process(self):
        num_train_per_class = self.num_train_per_class
        num_val = self.num_val
        num_test = self.num_test
        # Read data into huge `Data` list.
#         data_list = ['data']  # node classification do not neet to define data_list just data (one graph)
        data_list = self.data_list
        if self.pre_filter is not None:
            data_list = [data for data in data_list if self.pre_filter(data)]

        if self.pre_transform is not None:
            data_list = [self.pre_transform(data) for data in data_list]

        data, slices = self.collate(data_list)
        torch.save((data, slices), self.processed_paths[0])

3.使用自己的数据来训练并测试¶

这里使用自己的数据不是指使用自己的数据集，依然是使用cora数据集，但是不使用它封装好的dataset，也不使用我自己封装的dataset，而是直接来跑出结果，因为官网有这样一段话：

Do I really need to use these dataset interfaces? No! Just as in regular PyTorch, you do not have to use datasets, e.g., when you want to create synthetic data on the fly without saving them explicitly to disk. In this case, simply pass a regular python list holding torch_geometric.data.Data objects and pass them to torch_geometric.data.DataLoader: from torch_geometric.data import Data, DataLoader

data_list = [Data(...), ..., Data(...)] loader = DataLoader(data_list, batch_size=32)

因此，我将尝试这种方式直接训练和测试数据集。

# 5.2) 定义2层GCN的网络.
class Net(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(Net, self).__init__()
        self.conv1 = GCNConv(dataset.num_node_features, 16)
        self.conv2 = GCNConv(16, dataset.num_classes)

    def forward(self, data):
        x, edge_index = data.x, data.edge_index

        x = self.conv1(x, edge_index)
        x = F.relu(x)
        x = F.dropout(x, training=self.training)
        x = self.conv2(x, edge_index)

        return F.log_softmax(x, dim=1)

# 5.3) 训练 & 测试.
device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')
model = Net().to(device)
optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.01, weight_decay=5e-4)
# 训练模型
model.train()
for epoch in range(200):
    loss_all = 0
    for data in loader:
        data = data.to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        out = model(data)
#         print(output.shape)
        loss = F.nll_loss(out[data.train_mask], data.y[data.train_mask])
        loss.backward()
        loss_all += loss.item()
        optimizer.step()
    if epoch % 50 == 0:
        print(loss_all)
